# Gunner — Cursor Rules

## Repository & Folder Sync
- Local folder: `/Users/coreylavinder/Gunner`
- GitHub repo: `github.com/c7lavinder/Gunner`
- Deploy branch: `production` (Railway auto-deploys from this branch)
- Default branch: `main` (keep in sync with `production` after every meaningful session)
- These three must always match: local folder name = GitHub repo name = Railway project name = `Gunner`
- Never create sub-folders, scratch files, or debug scripts in the repo root — keep root clean

## Branch
Always work on `production`. Never commit directly to `main`.
Keep `main` in sync: after every working session, merge `production` into `main` and push both.

## Stack
- Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite (client/src/)
- Backend: Node.js + Express + tRPC (server/)
- DB: PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM — schema in drizzle/schema.ts
- Storage: Supabase Storage (gunner-recordings bucket)
- Deploy: Railway — auto-deploys on push to active branch

## Active Tenants
- ID=1: New Again Houses (primary, live)
- ID=450029: NAH Kitty Hawk (onboarding soon)
- ID=540044: Apex Property Solutions (demo)
- Never hardcode tenantId — always multi-tenant safe

## Env Vars
All secrets live in Railway env vars. Access via ENV object in server/_core/env.ts.
Never use raw process.env in business logic. Never hardcode keys.

## Before Every Push
1. `npx tsc --noEmit` → must be 0 errors
2. Commit with prefix: fix: / feat: / docs: / refactor:
3. Push to the active deploy branch only

## Key Files
- server/_core/env.ts — all environment variables
- server/routers/ — all API endpoints (split into 12 router files)
- drizzle/schema.ts — database schema (source of truth)
- server/_core/llm.ts — AI/LLM calls (OpenAI)
- server/services/grading.ts — AI call grading pipeline
- server/_core/storage.ts — Supabase file storage
- server/_core/email.ts — Resend email sending
- server/crm/ghl/ghlAdapter.ts — GHL CRM adapter

## Living Documents — Keep Updated
After completing meaningful work, update the relevant docs:
- SAAS-LIFECYCLE.md — Update the affected stage (status %, gaps, priority). Add a row to the Change Log.
- BUILD-STATUS.md — Move items from "What Remains" to "Completed Work" when done.
- CLAUDE.md — Update if directory structure, key files, or stack changes.
These docs are read by every AI agent. Stale docs = wasted work.

## Playbook Architecture — Non-Negotiable
The four-layer playbook chain (User > Tenant > Industry > Software) drives ALL labels, names,
stage colors, call types, KPI metrics, and terminology in the app.
- Frontend: always use `useTenantConfig()` — never hardcode strings that belong to the playbook
- Backend: always resolve through `server/services/playbooks.ts` resolver functions
- Full compliance rules: see `.cursor/rules/playbook-compliance.mdc`
- Open violations tracker: see `COMPLIANCE.md` in repo root

